  <statement>
      
      
      
      
      
      <p>
          For each of the following, classify the type of variable described as <em>Numerical</em> or <em>Categorical</em>, as well as the subcategory <em>Continuous</em>, <em>Discrete</em>, <em>Nominal</em> or <em>Ordinal</em>.  Be sure to justify your choices.
          <ol>
              <li>Classifying a person's income as Lower Income, Middle Income and Upper Income.</li>
              <li>The total snowfall in a city over a year in feet.</li>
              <li>The depreciation of a cars value over a decade in dollars.</li>
              <li>A response to a survey ranging from Strongly Agree to Strongly Disagree.</li>
              <li>How many items a party of four order in a restaurant.</li>
              <li>A choice of streaming services.</li>
          </ol>
          
      </p>
      
      
     
      
          
          
          
          
      
  </statement>
  <answer>
      <title>Partial Solution:</title>
      
      
      
      
     <p>
          <ol>
              <li>Categorical, Ordinal</li>
              <li>Numerical, Continuous</li>
              <li>Numerical, Continuous</li>
              <li>Categorical, Ordinal</li>
              <li>Numerical, Discrete</li>
              <li>Categorical, Nominal</li>
          </ol>
          
      </p>
          
      
  </answer>
</exercise>
